name: WomenSHealthTechnologyCRNProceduresPerformedGrouping
title: Women's Health Technology CRN Procedures Performed (Grouping)
description: Derived from Women's Health Technology Coordinated Registry Network harmonized values, this value set identifies procedures performed and is a grouping to allow inclusion of value sets from multiple code systems. This value set grouping includes eCQM Gynecological Surgery values sets (SNOMED CT and ICD10PCS).
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Women's Health),(Data Element Scope: This value set serves to identify whether a concept is included as a performed procedure.),(Inclusion Criteria: This value set includes the consensus, harmonized values.),(Exclusion Criteria: None)
